# API Contract Standards

## Contract Ownership
- All API request/response shapes MUST be defined in `packages/contracts/`
- The contracts package is the single source of truth for data shapes across backend and frontend
- Never define inline request/response types in route handlers or frontend code

## Type Generation
- Frontend TypeScript types are GENERATED from Pydantic models, never hand-written
- Generation runs as a build step (`scripts/generate_ts_types.py`), not manually
- API client imports from generated types only (`apps/web/src/types/`)
- Regenerate types after any contract model change — CI enforces this

## Backend Validation
- Route handlers validate input against contract models (Pydantic)
- Use `Body()`, `Query()`, `Path()` with Pydantic model types for automatic validation
- Return contract-defined response models from all endpoints
- Error responses follow the standard shape: `{"error": str, "code": str, "detail": any}`

## Frontend Consumption
- API client code lives in `apps/web/src/lib/apiClient.ts`
- All API calls use generated types for request params and response parsing
- No `any` types for API responses — always typed from contracts
- Handle error responses with typed error classification

## Versioning
- Contract models support additive changes (new optional fields) without breaking consumers
- Breaking changes require a new model version and migration path
- Schema backward compatibility is tested at the package level
